metadata.name: Geode #1
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - “slow=1”: Draw only one shape per frame.

metadata.name: Nuages possibles #89
metadata.description:
Stippling clouds imagined by a computer.

Each cloud is a "Nuage possible"

It may be generated from code,
but these clouds might have existed,
or might exist in the future,
just for a brief moment.


Those images were inspired by Joanie Lemercier’s cloud series, an algorithm is imagining more and more variations of those skyscapes in an infinite quest for the perfect cloud.

Once created from code, the drawings are made by a plotter machine, a little robot that moves a pen over black paper to lay down dots of white ink. The robot is like an extension of the artist’s arm, allowing him to create infinite iterations and variations.

The dots pattern and their density help create the illusion of shadows, gradients and brightness, a technique inherited from the pointillism movement, born in Belgium and France in the late 19th century.

metadata.name: 凹凸 -ou_totsu- #8
metadata.description:
凹凸 -ou_totsu- Asahamiz

コンクリートブロック塀を眺めていました。
その時、壁の開口から夕日の日差しが差し込み、
自分のいる壁側には、また別の光線が影を生み出していました。

その二つの光線の行く末を想像の中で追っていました。
そんな散歩のひと時が、
約５か月間の自分のコーディングの時間に変わっていきました。

壁面には棒と穴を配置しました。
棒には私側の光線の影、
穴からは向こう側からの光線が差し込みます。

棒と穴の配置はrowcol,zigzag,curve の３パターンが入り交ざります。

各Featuresのパターンは色んな遊び要素を取り入れています。


"s","d","f"キーでpng保存が可能です。
"s"_screensize
"d"_2400px * 2400px
"f"_3600px * 3600px

是非お楽しみください。

Asahamiz

metadata.name: Chaos #48
metadata.description:
Chaos seems to be the only constant thing in the universe. No matter the age, situation, location, success of any individual, from time to time, each one of us undergoes bouts of uncertainty. Chaos is something that is often portrayed in a negative light, but every once in a while it can end up being something beautiful as well. For example a nice surprise in an otherwise hectic day! 

This generative token is a celebration of chaos, a ray of hope amidst the tumultuous times that we live in, an escape from our internal vulnerabilities, a sense of closure and acceptance even when a lot might be going on in our lives. 

Feel free to mint as many as you want, gift it to your friends or loved ones, sell it, resell it or even make derivatives of your particular mint. I put in a reserve list for everybody who has collected any of my NFTs in the past so that my supporters don't miss out! This token is an expression of my gratitude to my supporters, and the entire FxHash community. Thank you all! 
Keep making art. No matter how hard today might be, be hopeful for a better tomorrow. 

Made with love in cables.gl

metadata.name: Magnolia Portrait #180
metadata.description:
Inspired by observation of the incessantly-rooted Pteridophyte and Magnolia, the cognominal series, “Magnolia”, portrays a manifestation of layers of constant streams crossing dynamically in a flow. Through years of growing in fluxed vapor, its knots and roots construct organized and rhythmic patterns within chaotic orders. From two-dimensional layouts to three-dimensional composition, “Magnolia” absorbs its fundamental image, and extend it even further — creating the core of generative artwork.

Press "s" to download

metadata.name: Smile_Bamboo #22
metadata.description:
From within a single acupuncture point, a trunk stretches out, like a bamboo, in a straight line and at different angles.

One leaf. And one round fruit.
It is like a smile, the one we are always looking for.

A smile is what I seek from day to day.
Just a straight, pure smile.

I felt as if I would lose such a natural expression as a human being at any moment.

I began to wish for a code, a number to smile at me again.

I can't draw faces in sketches well.
But I enjoyed reloading over and over again, hoping to find a smile somewhere in the randomness of this code.


May the world be filled with smiles.
That is all I pray for.

Asahamiz
